1.5 Accidental Release Prevention Program and Process Safety Information (Appendix B of the RMP)

COY maintains a variety of technical documents that are used to help ensure safe operations of the WPS regulated process.  These documents address the physical properties of hazardous substances handled at their facility, operating parameters of the systems, and equipment operating procedures for these processes.  COY ensures that this process safety information is available to its employees and the outside emergency responders.

International Chemical Safety Cards are produced by the international safety community and are cosponsored by the National Institute for Occupational Safety and Health (NIOSH).  This resource is intended to provide health and safety information for workers potentially in contact with regulated substances.  The International Chemical Safety Cards for chlorine are provided in Appendix B of the RMP. 

Material Safety Data Sheets (MSDSs) document the physical properties of hazardous substances handled at COY, including chlorine gas used at the WFP facility. The MSDSs for chlorine gas is presented in Appendix B of the RMP.  The information available on the MSDSs for each hazardous substance typically includes:

? toxicity information and permissible exposure limits
? physical data (e.g., boiling point, melting point, flash point)
? reactivity and corrosivity data
? thermal and chemical stability data
? hazards of mixing substances in the process

MSDSs for regulated substances handled at this facility are available at the Water Managers
